miscConds.notes:
During the pendency of this deferral, the Defendant agrees to:
-Commit no acts which rise to the level of probable cause in violation of the criminal laws of the state of Wisconsin, or of any other state, or of the United States of America.
-Comply with all conditions of bail or bond in this case.
-Pay a fine of $200. 
-Comply with all conditions of probation counts 2 and 3 of this case. Violation of any rule of probation, or revocation from probation, constitutes a violation of this condition. Violation of probation may still be grounds for termination of this agreement. All terms and conditions of probation and sex offender conditions must be followed. 
-Pay restitution in the amount of $1328.79, which the Defendant stipulates he or she owes in this matter, not including the 10% surcharge. The defendant will make monthly payments of $50 per month, on the first day of every month, payable to the Douglas County Clerk of Courts.
If the defendant makes good faith efforts to pay the restitution but later encounters hardship on making scheduled payments, it is the responsibility of the defendant, either personally or through his or her attorney, to contact the District Attorney's Office at 715-395-1218 to request and extension. Failure to request an extension in this circumstance constitutes evidence that the defendant has no made good faith efforts to make scheduled payment(s). The District Attorney's Office has sole discretion whether to modify the agreed-upon payment schedule. A missed or late restitution payment constitutes a violation of this condition.

-The parties agree, and the defendant understands, that the conditions of any bail or bond in effect on the plea date shall continue for the entire length of this agreement, and that any violation of the defendant's bond may result in bail jumping charges pursuant to Wis. Stat. 946.49. The defendant further understands that a charged violation of the bail or bond for which probable cause is found shall be a basis for the State to vacate this agreement.
-Defendant will keep Douglas County Clerk of Courts informed of his address and telephone number at all times, and stipulates that the sending of notice by regular mail to the address on file with the Clerk of Courts constitutes sufficient notice of any court hearings scheduled in this matter.  The non-appearance of the defendant may result in the issuance of an arrest warrant. 
-If, at any time during the deferral period, the defendant has no complied with the conditions of this agreement, the State may at its discretion and upon notice the defendant, revoke the agreement and move the Court to enter judgment of conviction and the parties shall proceed to sentencing. At sentencing, the State shall be free to argue for any disposition it deems appropriate, up to and including the maximum sentence provided by law. The defendant is further notified that entry of the Judgment of Conviction in this case will result in the collateral consequence of Offender Registration for the remainder of the defendant's life.  
-Except as otherwise provided in this agreement, the State must prove non-compliance with thus agreement by the preponderance of the evidence at a hearing subject to Wis. Stat. 911.01(4)(c).
-At the end of this deferral period or upon completion of all terms of this agreement, whichever is later, if the defendant has complied with the conditions of this agreement and provided proof of compliance when required, the State will move to dismiss Count 1 with prejudice.

result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Landan William Swenson

records.addlTxt: No contact with Victim 1. No intentional contact with minors.

2:24 PM Defendant Landan William Swenson in court.  Attorney Nathan M Cockerham in court for Landan William Swenson.  Attorney Angela M Wilson in court for State of Wisconsin. Court calls case. State indicates will plead guilty to counts 1, 2, and 3 in 22CF61 and DRI on 22CF218. Asks for a deferred agreement as to count 1, and for counts 2 and 3, sentence withheld for 3 years probation, with conditions of DOC programming, $100 fine on each count plus costs, concurrent, no contact with Victim. Attorney Cockerham indicates will be a no contest plea. 
Court recounts charges and possible penalties. Defendant pleads no contest. Court informs defendant of rights given up by their plea. Attorney stipulates to a factual basis. Court accepts the Defendant's plea and finds that the Defendant's plea has been freely, voluntarily and intelligently made. Court finds Defendant understands all the rights they are waiving by their plea. The Defendant is found guilty and Judgment of Conviction is deferred on Count 1 and entered on Counts 2 and 3. Everything else dismissed but read it. DA will monitor agreement.
State makes statements regarding sentencing. Asking court not to order expungement due to nature of the case. Society will be harmed if expunged, needs to be kept on his record. Victim still suffering. Points out inconsistencies in evaluation. 
Attorney Cockerham argues for expungement. Argues special disposition statute. Participated in evaluation on a voluntary basis, it was not mandatory for this agreement. Asking for expungement upon completion, will and already has had consequences from this matter. 
State and defense agree to no sex offender registry.  Defendant makes statements. 

Court orders sentence withheld on counts 2 and 3, for 3 years probation, conditions to include $100 fine plus costs on each count, DOC programming, no contact with Victim.

Court makes statements regarding expungement. Society must be protected. Court not 100% convinced that society will not be harmed. Court does not approve expungement. 

Bail to be converted to $5000 signature bond.

01:56 PM Defendant Landan William Swenson in court with attorney Nathan M Cockerham and not in-custody.  Peter James Marvin Kruger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant's address confirmed.  Attorney/defendant acknowledges receipt of criminal complaint, waives reading. Court will set matter for Prelim.   States request on bail: $1500 cash bail with conditions of no contact with victim 1. State indicates that while defendant does not have a criminal history, give the allegations against him, cash bail is warranted. 
Atty Cockerham asserts that defendant does not have prior criminal history therefore, no missed appearances. Defendant does appear here today voluntarily. Defendant does have strong family ties to Douglas County. Defendant did cooperate with law enforcement and request signature bond and does not have objection to the conditions. Defendant is able to post $2000 if the Court orders it.
Court weighs all factors. This is a Class C felony and the Court has serious concerns regarding allegations alledged against defendant. Court Orders $2000 cash bail with conditions of no contact with victim 1 as listed in the ID Key. No intentional contact with minors  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 9, 2022 at 08:15 am.
